The LCES  Legal Calculus Educational System sequence can be applied to almost any problem.

It is a framework of procedural literacy:

Blueprint. Research. Construct. Challenge. Decide.

Why use multiple AI systems instead of one?

Because a single system tends to merge issue-framing, research, drafting, and self-defense into one stream.

LCES separates those functions.

One AI helps build the blueprint.  
One helps research and test support.  
One helps construct the work product.  
One helps challenge it.

That separation reduces drift, exposes weakness, and makes the workflow more adversarial, structured, and reviewable before a human decides.

The goal is not more AI.

The goal is better process.

